Docker has 5 network types:

Bridge (default) — Containers on the same host communicate via a virtual network. Most common for local dev.
Host — Container shares the host's network directly. No isolation, best for performance.
None — No networking at all. Container is completely isolated.
Overlay — Connects containers across multiple hosts (used in Docker Swarm).
Macvlan — Assigns a real MAC address to container, making it appear as a physical device on the network.

Most used in practice:

Single host dev/testing  → Bridge
High performance needed  → Host
Multi-host production    → Overlay

# List all networks
docker network ls

# Create bridge network
docker network create my-network
